WEBVTT

00:00.898 --> 00:02.602
<i>Previously on "Gotham"...</i>

00:02.664 --> 00:04.897
Hugo Strange can fix Butch.

00:04.932 --> 00:07.814
Strange might be my only hope, Tabby.

00:07.874 --> 00:10.175
Whatever happens
after I walk out that door,

00:10.246 --> 00:12.112
I care about you,

00:12.137 --> 00:13.636
and I always will.

00:13.672 --> 00:14.971
JEREMIAH: Jerome is dead.

00:15.006 --> 00:16.439
Long live me.

00:16.475 --> 00:18.541
(explosion)

00:18.577 --> 00:19.709
Oh, my God!

00:19.744 --> 00:21.911
I have bombs planted around the city.

00:21.947 --> 00:23.580
GORDON: These are the buildings
Jeremiah's planning

00:23.615 --> 00:24.948
to demolish with his bombs.

00:24.983 --> 00:26.616
Once those buildings are blown,

00:26.651 --> 00:28.918
they collapse and create the labyrinth
from the finished drawing.

00:29.262 --> 00:30.658
GORDON: I have the locations

00:30.683 --> 00:32.555
of every bomb Jeremiah planted.

00:35.236 --> 00:37.093
How did they beat you, huh?

00:37.128 --> 00:38.461
I'll have to start again.

00:38.497 --> 00:39.762
RA'S AL GHUL: I had a vision.

00:39.798 --> 00:42.232
Of Gotham in flames.

00:42.267 --> 00:43.233
Together,

00:43.268 --> 00:44.567
we can make that happen.

00:44.603 --> 00:45.735
Now listen closely

00:45.770 --> 00:47.003
to what you must do.

00:47.038 --> 00:48.771
(gunshot)

00:50.542 --> 00:51.508
Hold on, Selina.

00:51.543 --> 00:53.576
(Alfred grunting)

00:54.455 --> 00:57.213
(Bruce muttering) It's okay. It's okay.

00:58.350 --> 01:00.517
- Make way.
- We'll do everything we can,

01:00.552 --> 01:02.952
but the evacuation has us
dealing with a skeleton crew.

01:02.988 --> 01:04.953
- Bruce.
- Selina.

01:04.989 --> 01:06.456
I'm right here. You're at the hospital.

01:06.491 --> 01:07.757
You're gonna be okay.

01:07.792 --> 01:09.425
Are you gonna leave me?

01:09.461 --> 01:11.027
No.

01:11.062 --> 01:12.462
No, I'm gonna be right here.

01:12.497 --> 01:13.997
You promise?

01:14.929 --> 01:16.929
I promise.

01:23.671 --> 01:26.271
(metal clanging)

01:33.326 --> 01:35.490
You know, I don't know
why I brought him here.

01:36.050 --> 01:39.051
I should've killed him
when I had the chance.

01:39.312 --> 01:40.978
You did the right thing, Alfred.

01:41.053 --> 01:42.187
You say that.

01:42.222 --> 01:44.556
You didn't see what he did to Selina.

01:46.293 --> 01:47.759
Right. I better get to the hospital.

01:47.795 --> 01:49.695
I'll stop by when I can.

01:49.730 --> 01:51.695
Alfred.

01:52.232 --> 01:54.199
He couldn't have put
a cap in that psycho,

01:54.234 --> 01:56.335
- done the world a favor?
- Where are we?

01:56.370 --> 01:58.355
Bomb squad's at the
last site on the map.

01:58.402 --> 01:59.871
After they disarm the
bomb, they're gonna put it

01:59.907 --> 02:01.039
in a warehouse with all the others.

02:01.075 --> 02:02.708
Also, the mayor called.

02:02.743 --> 02:04.760
He wants to lift the evacuation order.

02:04.807 --> 02:06.244
Tell him we're not doing anything

02:06.280 --> 02:08.747
until we have all the bombs locked away.

02:10.306 --> 02:12.057
Pardon me, Jim.

02:17.658 --> 02:19.625
Don't you all have work to do?

02:20.995 --> 02:22.961
(indistinct muttering)

02:25.065 --> 02:26.632
What is it?

02:26.667 --> 02:29.502
I'd like to press charges
against Bruce Wayne's butler.

02:30.731 --> 02:33.065
I mean, just look at my face.

02:33.132 --> 02:34.388
I think you look great.

02:34.442 --> 02:37.709
And I'd like to speak to Bruce again.

02:37.745 --> 02:39.244
We couldn't really talk before,

02:39.279 --> 02:42.247
what with his girlfriend
bleeding out all over him.

02:44.351 --> 02:47.552
You tried to prove
you're better than your brother.

02:47.588 --> 02:49.554
But I'm still here.

02:49.590 --> 02:51.289
The city's still here.

02:51.325 --> 02:53.492
You're a failure, Jeremiah.

02:54.157 --> 02:55.460
Enjoy Arkham.

02:55.496 --> 02:57.629
Your brother did. Put him in the box.

02:57.665 --> 02:59.112
Get him ready for transport.

02:59.137 --> 03:01.776
Bring me Bruce Wayne, and I'll tell you
where the other bombs are.

03:03.137 --> 03:04.803
We have all your bombs.

03:04.838 --> 03:06.605
The maze bombs, yes.

03:06.640 --> 03:09.441
I mean the other ones.

03:10.644 --> 03:11.943
Jim...

03:12.464 --> 03:15.347
as an engineer, you expect systems

03:15.382 --> 03:16.682
to fail, so...

03:16.717 --> 03:18.782
you build in redundancies.

03:20.287 --> 03:22.790
And I am a very good engineer.

03:24.625 --> 03:26.925
- You're bluffing.
- Am I?

03:27.553 --> 03:30.885
How many lives are you willing to bet?

03:31.498 --> 03:33.131
You're right, you know.

03:33.775 --> 03:35.634
I did fail.

03:35.669 --> 03:38.410
I didn't yet understand
the vision I was servicing,

03:38.435 --> 03:40.539
but I do now.

03:40.574 --> 03:44.122
My eyes are open, as will yours be.

03:48.549 --> 03:50.949
When you realize I'm not bluffing,

03:50.984 --> 03:53.122
bring me Bruce Wayne.

03:53.854 --> 03:55.721
And I'd like a coffee.

03:55.756 --> 03:59.057
Black. Two sugars.

03:59.093 --> 04:00.392
(sustained beeping)

04:00.427 --> 04:03.165
No heartbeat.

04:03.697 --> 04:06.531
Extraordinary.

04:07.215 --> 04:08.814
This better work.

04:08.875 --> 04:10.902
The chemicals
that turned him into this...

04:11.557 --> 04:13.872
beautiful specimen

04:13.907 --> 04:16.975
kept his organs surprisingly
well preserved.

04:17.010 --> 04:20.545
Once we flush his body with antitoxin,

04:20.581 --> 04:21.913
we'll top him off

04:21.949 --> 04:23.849
- with some fresh blood.
- (whimpering)

04:23.884 --> 04:26.752
And a quick jolt to the heart

04:26.787 --> 04:29.781
will see him good as new.

04:34.394 --> 04:36.528
You hear that?

04:36.563 --> 04:38.163
You're gonna be cured.

04:38.198 --> 04:40.122
- Yeah.
- (phone ringing)

04:43.251 --> 04:45.417
What?

04:45.500 --> 04:46.709
When?

04:46.807 --> 04:48.340
What is it?

04:49.211 --> 04:51.676
Selina's been shot
by that lunatic Jeremiah.

04:51.712 --> 04:52.911
She's at Gotham General.

04:52.946 --> 04:54.846
I have to go. I'll be back.

04:54.882 --> 04:56.081
Of course.

04:56.116 --> 04:57.682
You go check on the kid.

04:57.718 --> 04:59.684
What? No, she's in surgery.

04:59.720 --> 05:01.186
I'm gonna kill Jeremiah.

05:01.221 --> 05:02.728
I'll come with you.

05:02.813 --> 05:04.623
- I don't advise that. The procedure
- (groans)

05:04.649 --> 05:06.610
should not be interrupted.

05:06.727 --> 05:08.392
Stay.

05:08.495 --> 05:10.853
I'll be here...

05:11.098 --> 05:13.799
making sure everything goes as planned.

05:14.639 --> 05:18.509
I'm doing this for Butch, not for you.

05:21.408 --> 05:23.141
(softly): It's okay.

05:30.484 --> 05:32.450
(siren wailing in distance)

05:34.154 --> 05:35.754
Unfortunately, there's no telling

05:35.789 --> 05:38.223
just how many battery bombs
Jeremiah produced.

05:38.258 --> 05:40.692
He was fanatically secret
about his technology,

05:40.727 --> 05:41.827
and Bruce trusted him, so...

05:41.862 --> 05:43.829
He's gotta be bluffing.

05:43.864 --> 05:45.363
- (knock on door)
- Yeah?

05:45.399 --> 05:47.532
Cap, mayor's on the phone again.

05:47.568 --> 05:49.134
The evacuation stays in effect.

05:49.169 --> 05:50.815
I will tell him when it's lifted.

05:52.306 --> 05:53.638
LUCIUS: <i>You think there are more bombs?</i>

05:53.674 --> 05:56.341
Up till now, Jeremiah's actions sprang

05:56.376 --> 05:58.410
from the fear and hatred of his brother.

05:58.445 --> 05:59.678
Even his obsession with Bruce

05:59.713 --> 06:01.954
is just a reflection of Jerome's.

06:02.728 --> 06:04.249
What did he mean when he said

06:04.284 --> 06:06.918
he didn't understand
the vision he was serving?

06:06.954 --> 06:09.154
That his eyes had been opened?

06:10.891 --> 06:12.324
YORK: Perhaps the previous mayor

06:12.359 --> 06:14.025
took orders from a police captain.

06:14.061 --> 06:16.161
- Sir, Captain Gordon is...
- Jim Gordon is not

06:16.196 --> 06:18.597
the mayor of Gotham; I am.

06:18.632 --> 06:21.466
The people need to know
the city is safe.

06:21.501 --> 06:22.651
I'm lifting the order.

06:25.190 --> 06:26.605
What are you looking at?

06:26.640 --> 06:28.039
There's a man on the building

06:28.075 --> 06:29.841
across the street, staring at us.

06:29.877 --> 06:30.842
What?

